    "body": "### Problem\r\nHeaders presync computes `m_max_commitments` from the elapsed time since the chain-start MTP plus `MAX_FUTURE_BLOCK_TIME`.\r\nWhen the local clock is more than `MAX_FUTURE_BLOCK_TIME` behind that MTP, the elapsed value is negative, but it is then used in arithmetic that assigns to the unsigned commitment cap.\r\nThis can turn the intended zero bound into a large cap and let low-work headers presync continue instead of aborting at the first commitment.\r\n\r\n### Fix\r\nKeep the elapsed-time value signed and assign an explicit zero commitment cap when the chain-start MTP is still too far in the future for a locally acceptable extension to exist.\r\nThe first stored commitment then exceeds the cap and aborts presync.\r\n\r\nThe unit test covers this boundary with `commitment_period=1`, and the `headers_sync_state` fuzz target now also allows the same clock-skew case instead of always choosing a time at or after the chain-start MTP.",
